track.name: Wang Dang Doodle
comments: I saw Koko in a dive bar 3 blocks from were I live now with Matt Murphy on lead she pitched the wang dang doodle for sure.  You are so right about everybody was everybody's good friend by the end of the night

Went to a small blues club for New Years one year where Koko was the headliner. Not only could she shout the blues, but she flat knew how to get down and have a good time. It was like you were at a house party and everyone was her best friend.
that's because your name tells the story dope a- - version  my a - -
sing it out all night long ........... great stuff

Often covered, never surpassed.  Willie Dixon wrote it and said he didn't like it, but what's not to like?  Fierce vocals, great backing vocals (from Dixon), rollicking, jaunty rhythm, stinging guitar...  This is what mid-century blues was all about...
I swear when I hear this song. I sing it "all  night  long"  Love this snappy little tune, ..... great version............ Love the sax solo.
Here we go it is saturday night
